# Senior Software Engineer - Full Stack Development

## Company: TechVision Solutions
**Location:** San Francisco, CA (Hybrid - 3 days onsite)  
**Type:** Full-time  
**Experience Level:** 5-7 years  
**Salary Range:** $140,000 - $180,000

---

## About Us

TechVision Solutions is a rapidly growing SaaS company specializing in cloud-based enterprise solutions. We serve over 500 Fortune 1000 companies and are committed to innovation, scalability, and exceptional user experiences. Our engineering team of 50+ developers works in an agile environment with cutting-edge technologies.

---

## Job Description

We are seeking an experienced **Senior Software Engineer** to join our platform engineering team. You will be responsible for designing, developing, and maintaining scalable web applications that serve millions of users daily. This role requires expertise in both frontend and backend technologies, with a strong focus on system architecture and performance optimization.

---

## Key Responsibilities

- Design and develop high-performance, scalable web applications using React, Node.js, and Python
- Architect and implement RESTful APIs and microservices for enterprise-level systems
- Lead code reviews and mentor junior developers on best practices
- Collaborate with cross-functional teams including Product, Design, and DevOps
- Optimize application performance, ensuring 99.9% uptime and fast response times
- Implement comprehensive testing strategies including unit, integration, and end-to-end tests
- Participate in on-call rotation and troubleshoot production issues
- Contribute to technical documentation and system design decisions
- Stay current with emerging technologies and propose improvements to our tech stack
- Work with AWS cloud infrastructure including EC2, S3, Lambda, and RDS

---

## Required Qualifications

### Technical Skills
- **5+ years** of professional software development experience
- Strong proficiency in **JavaScript/TypeScript** and modern frameworks (**React**, **Vue.js**, or **Angular**)
- Expert knowledge of **Node.js** and backend development
- Experience with **Python** for backend services and data processing
- Solid understanding of **SQL databases** (PostgreSQL, MySQL) and **NoSQL** (MongoDB, Redis)
- Hands-on experience with **AWS** cloud services and infrastructure
- Proficiency with **Docker** and **Kubernetes** for containerization
- Strong knowledge of **Git** version control and CI/CD pipelines
- Experience with **RESTful API** design and **GraphQL**
- Understanding of system design patterns and software architecture principles

### Soft Skills
- Excellent problem-solving and analytical thinking abilities
- Strong communication skills with ability to explain complex technical concepts
- Experience working in **Agile/Scrum** environments
- Proven ability to mentor and guide junior developers
- Self-motivated with strong time management skills
- Collaborative mindset with ability to work across teams

---

## Preferred Qualifications

- Experience with **microservices architecture** and event-driven systems
- Knowledge of **Apache Kafka** or similar message brokers
- Familiarity with **Terraform** or other Infrastructure as Code (IaC) tools
- Experience with monitoring tools like **Datadog**, **New Relic**, or **Grafana**
- Background in **machine learning** or **data engineering**
- Open source contributions or technical blog writing
- Bachelor's or Master's degree in Computer Science or related field
- Experience with **mobile development** (React Native, Flutter)
- Knowledge of **security best practices** and OWASP guidelines
- Familiarity with **WebSocket** and real-time communication protocols

---

## Technical Stack

**Frontend:**
- React 18, TypeScript, Redux Toolkit
- Material-UI, Tailwind CSS
- Jest, React Testing Library

**Backend:**
- Node.js (Express, NestJS)
- Python (FastAPI, Django)
- GraphQL (Apollo Server)

**Database:**
- PostgreSQL, MongoDB, Redis

**Cloud & DevOps:**
- AWS (EC2, S3, Lambda, RDS, CloudFront)
- Docker, Kubernetes, Helm
- Jenkins, GitHub Actions
- Terraform

**Monitoring & Tools:**
- Datadog, Sentry
- Jira, Confluence
- Slack, Zoom

